The Nasarawa State Governor, Alhaji Abdullahi Sule, has urged practicing journalists in the state to uphold the ethics of journalism by being accurate and objective in their reportage. The governor made the appeal in his maiden interaction with journalists yesterday at the government House in Lafia, the state capital. According to him:“My administration is determined to work hand in hand in a cordial manner with the press in order to move the state forward developmentally. My door will be always open up for you to contribute immensely to my administration through your meaningful ideas for me tosucceed.”  He continued:“You media organizations play critical and most vital role for society or nation building.